&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a motivated and detail-oriented OTC Trader with 2-8 years of trading experience, preferably in the cryptocurrency market. The ideal candidate will possess a solid understanding of options and other financial derivatives and be knowledgeable about options pricing, greeks and gamma hedging. While OTC trading experience is appreciated, it is not a requirement. This role involves clear communication with clients and internal teams, as well as a strong capability to manage financial risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute OTC trades in a timely and efficient manner, ensuring compliance with internal policies including pricing and trading policies and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor market trends and analyze trading opportunities, utilizing a decent understanding of options and financial derivatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with clients and internal stakeholders to coordinate trading strategies and initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain high levels of attention to detail in all aspects of trading, documentation, and compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough risk assessments to ensure financial risk is managed comfortably.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team members to share insights, discuss what best solutions to provide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize trading algorithms on a daily basis to hedge derivatives and execute client transactions. The trader will also play a key role in monitoring and enhancing these algorithms to optimize performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
